parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OCS sensor can cause the passenger airbag to be deactivated, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag off light is displayed
the airbag light blinks on the dashboard
and the passenger airbag is deactivated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, and lack acceleration, making it difficult to drive safely, especially on hills and highways.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and acceleration
hesitates
and lacks acceleration

especially when driving uphill or on hot days; the vehicle slows down or stops responding to the gas pedal; the RPMs may increase but the transmission does not engage; the vehicle may jerk or shake when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch and Transmission Hydraulic System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, making it difficult to drive safely, especially on hills and highways.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and acceleration

especially when driving uphill or on hot days; the vehicle slows down or stops responding to the gas pedal; the RPMs may increase but the transmission does not engage; the vehicle may jerk or shake when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause various issues, including burning odors, air conditioning malfunctions, and alarm system failures, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Burning odors
air conditioning malfunctions
alarm system failures
and failure of electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the door lock actuator can cause doors to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, which can be a safety hazard.
symptoms: Doors failing to open from the outside
doors only opening from the inside
and difficulty entering or exiting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air bag system can cause the air bag light to illuminate, indicating a potential safety risk, and may lead to expensive repairs.
symptoms: Air bag light illumination
failure of passenger side air bag
and need for expensive repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Vehicle failing to start
ignition switch malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
engine failure
and burning odors.
